{
  "stem": "9262.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And people had to do the cleaning for sanitation, for the removal of certain goods.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We had to work on the rails.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This was forced.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The Germans would pick up, you know, randomly in the street and put people to work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I was picked up and was given a shovel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we had to get the rail section from one side of the road over to the others, meaning that the tram car that was entering the ghetto, or the main road of the ghetto, to go through could not shunt.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Shunting means when the rail goes from one to the other.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So here, it had to go straight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So the shunting had to be diverted, had to be taken off.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the shunting was done outside-- outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And this was just to let the tram car go through the ghetto, because there was the bridge already.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we could go over the bridge.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Poles-- Polish tram car drivers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They went through, and the people were inside.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They could see into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the beginning, they said, whenever a tram car approaches, you must make yourself scarce.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Otherwise, you will be shot dead.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You're not allowed to see them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So each time a tram car came through, we had to make ourselves scarce-- run into one of the [INAUDIBLE] or to one of the houses.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then the tram car only went into two directions, like it went to one street which was called [POLISH] Street.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other one was called [POLISH] Street.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These were the two main thoroughfares where the tram cars went through.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was really very strange, because our street was one side of that road.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my aunt was living across the road.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
